        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 9:46PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 946 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Roduco, or 8 miles northwest of Gatesville, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, heavy rain, and frequent
lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Reduced visibility and minor flooding
possible. Frequent cloud to ground lightning strikes.

Locations impacted include...
Gatesville, Sunbury, South Mills, Holland, Chesapeake, Suffolk,
Gates, Como, Morgans Corner, Roduco, Hobbsville, Whaleyville,
Corapeake, Horseshoe, Savage, Peach, Suffolk Airport, Topsy,
Buckland, and Nicanor.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
